<a name="Evaluation-1"></a>
<h3 class="section">1.6 Evaluation</h3>
<a name="index-Evaluation"></a>

<p>When the Lisp interpreter works on an expression, the term for the
activity is called <em>evaluation</em>.  We say that the interpreter
&ldquo;evaluates the expression&rdquo;.  I&rsquo;ve used this term several times before.
The word comes from its use in everyday language, &ldquo;to ascertain the
value or amount of; to appraise&rdquo;, according to <cite>Webster&rsquo;s New
Collegiate Dictionary</cite>.
</p>
