<a name="A-Few-More-Complex-Functions"></a>
<h2 class="chapter">5 A Few More Complex Functions</h2>

<p>In this chapter, we build on what we have learned in previous chapters
by looking at more complex functions.  The <code>copy-to-buffer</code>
function illustrates use of two <code>save-excursion</code> expressions in
one definition, while the <code>insert-buffer</code> function illustrates
use of an asterisk in an <code>interactive</code> expression, use of
<code>or</code>, and the important distinction between a name and the object
to which the name refers.
</p>
<table class="menu" border="0" cellspacing="0">
<tr><td align="left" valign="top">&bull; <a href="#copy_002dto_002dbuffer" accesskey="1">copy-to-buffer</a>:</td><td>&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td align="left" valign="top">With <code>set-buffer</code>, <code>get-buffer-create</code>.
</td></tr>
<tr><td align="left" valign="top">&bull; <a href="#insert_002dbuffer" accesskey="2">insert-buffer</a>:</td><td>&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td align="left" valign="top">Read-only, and with <code>or</code>.
</td></tr>
<tr><td align="left" valign="top">&bull; <a href="#beginning_002dof_002dbuffer" accesskey="3">beginning-of-buffer</a>:</td><td>&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td align="left" valign="top">Shows <code>goto-char</code>,
                                <code>point-min</code>, and <code>push-mark</code>.
</td></tr>
<tr><td align="left" valign="top">&bull; <a href="#Second-Buffer-Related-Review" accesskey="4">Second Buffer Related Review</a>:</td><td>&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td align="left" valign="top">
</td></tr>
<tr><td align="left" valign="top">&bull; <a href="#optional-Exercise" accesskey="5">optional Exercise</a>:</td><td>&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td align="left" valign="top">
</td></tr>
