<a name="Save-your-time_003a-dolist-and-dotimes"></a>
<h3 class="section">11.2 Save your time: <code>dolist</code> and <code>dotimes</code></h3>

<p>In addition to <code>while</code>, both <code>dolist</code> and <code>dotimes</code>
provide for looping.  Sometimes these are quicker to write than the
equivalent <code>while</code> loop.  Both are Lisp macros.  (See <a href="http://www.gnu.org/software/emacs/manual/html_mono/elisp.html#Macros">Macros</a> in <cite>The GNU Emacs Lisp Reference Manual</cite>. )
</p>
<p><code>dolist</code> works like a <code>while</code> loop that <small>CDR</small>s down a
list:  <code>dolist</code> automatically shortens the list each time it
loops&mdash;takes the <small>CDR</small> of the list&mdash;and binds the <small>CAR</small> of
each shorter version of the list to the first of its arguments.
</p>
<p><code>dotimes</code> loops a specific number of times: you specify the number.
</p>
